node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'THE DIFFERENCE MOTIVATION VS DISCIPLINE MOTIVATION Motivation comes from the natural human drive to achieve something. Motivation doesn't last forever no matter how much you want something. It's a temporary effect created by the brain to boost you in the right direction. DISCIPLINE Discipline is the ability to continue pushing in the right direction when you no longer have motivation doing it for you. Discipline is far more important than motivation and you should NEVER rely on motivation only. THEBUSINESSHACKS'.

node.text:
The difference between motivation and discipline.
-
You need both. Motivation gets you started, discipline keeps you going.
-
Follow @thebusinesshacks for more.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @richardyuzee. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 2. Wake up and go to bed at the same time every day. Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @richardyuzee. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 3. Work hard now and make short term sacrifices for your long term goal and the tuture life you want.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @richardyuzee. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 4. Work out MINIMUM 3 times a week to train your body, but more importantly, train your mind Exercising regularly builds discipline, resilience and increases your energy. The key is to be consistent with it.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @richardyuzee. May be an image of text that says 'Richard Yu @richardyuzee 5. How you do one thing is how you do everything. node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace How built a multi 7-figure amazon business after getting laid off from my job. You might want to save this. [THREAD]'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I don't want to bore you with my story so I'll keep it short. got laid off from my job in 2017, and there was nothing could do about it. started selling on Amazon because needed to put food on the table and had a kid on the way.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I only ended up using $3k to start. I bought a course from some guy with a Lambo and it it was clear that he didn't sell on Amazon. It didn't help much and had to learn everything from scratch.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Now to the fun part. I had three products fail before had one successful product. I took the every ast dollar made from that product and reinvested it back into the business. My family was even surviving off of credit card points at one point.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I almost completely lost my ousiness a few months later. I tried launching 2 products, and ran out of cash to buy inventory. I had to let go of both of my new products and refilled the inventory on my first product. I got too greedy and paid the price.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Since then, I've learned my lesson. Never scale too quickly and always take things one step at a time. I've been building this business for 3 years now and still reinvest 40% of my profits back into the business. Even after 3 years, it's barely gotten to the $100k/m profit point.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace So what essons can you take away from this? 1. Don't scale too quickly. 2. Don't overestimate your abilities. 3. Take things one step at a time. 4. Chasing short-term wins can hurt you long-term. 5. Learn from others who have done it, but always look for ways to mprove'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I've built my Amazon FBA business to $250k/ rev and $100k/m profit. If wasn't so focused on getting rich quick when started, I'd probably be at $500k/m. Hopefully you don't make the same mistakes that made.'.

Photo shared by Entrepreneurship | Business on August 18, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace P.S. Here's a bonus if you've made it this far. The products that had to let go of when scaled too quickly are... Baby shower decorations and felt letter boards. Follow me if you want to learn more about Amazon FBA!'.
